TITLE: Eagles' Darius Slay tweets he is staying in Philadelphia: 'Back like I never left'
SUMMARY: After a day-long discussion, the Eagles seemed to have found a way to keep five-time Pro Bowl defensive back Darius Slay with the team.

TITLE: Large Russian city's anti-Putin former mayor jailed for 14 days pending trial
SUMMARY: Former Yekaterinburg, Russia, Mayor Yevgeny Roizman, a prominent critic of President Vladimir Putin was ordered to spend 14 days in jail pending trial.

TITLE: 7 killed in mysterious northern Iraq helicopter crash
SUMMARY: Seven people were killed Wednesday night in a mysterious northern Iraq helicopter crash. The helicopter was carrying militants that belonged to the outlawed Kurdistan Worker's Party.

TITLE: Montana attorney general to sue Biden administration over gun executive order
SUMMARY: Republican Montana Attorney General Austin Knudsen is preparing a lawsuit to fight the Biden administration's over its gun violence executive order

TITLE: Train hauling corn syrup derails in Arizona; no injuries reported
SUMMARY: A freight train hauling corn syrup derailed in a rural, nonresidential area of Arizona. The cause of the derailment, which involved eight cars, is unknown.

TITLE: NYC newspaper editor arrested for alleged police interference at Capitol riot
SUMMARY: Elliot Resnick, former chief editor of the New York City-based Jewish Press, has been arrested for his alleged role in the Jan. 6, 2021 Capitol riot.

TITLE: Tennessee looks at lowering permitless gun carry age to 18
SUMMARY: Tennessee gun rights activists are pushing to lower the age limit for the state's permitless concealed carry law, and state officials appear open to possible legislation.

TITLE: Def Leppard's drummer Rick Allen attacked by 19-year-old: police
SUMMARY: Def Leppard drumer Rick Allen was attacked outside of a Florida hotel by a 19-year-old on March 13, according to a police report obtained by Fox News Digital.

TITLE: Kamala Harris roasted for dodging Colbert's question on her role as VP: 'We're all wondering that'
SUMMARY: "Outnumbered" panelists called Vice President Kamala Harris a "drag" on the administration and suggested she may not know what her responsibilities are.

TITLE: Maryland overcomes slow start to bounce West Virginia from March Madness
SUMMARY: Maryland overcame a slow start against West Virginia to win 67-65 in the first round of the NCAA Men's Basketball Tournament on Thursday.

TITLE: Oklahoma man gets early release, commits triple homicide, cuts woman's heart out
SUMMARY: Lawrence Paul Anderson had been serving a 20 year drug-related sentence, but was recommended for early release by the OK Pardon and Parole Board

TITLE: Russian leadership ordered fighter jet pilots to be aggressive when intercepting US drone: sources
SUMMARY: Russian leadership ordered Su-27 fighter jet pilots on Tuesday to be aggressive in intercepting the U.S. military drone that one jet collided with,

SUMMARY: Two-time Emmy-nominated actress Christina Ricci spoke out about being threatened with a lawsuit over her unwillingness to participate in a sex scene early in her career.

TITLE: Sen. Rand Paul walks out of Homeland Security hearing after butting heads with Democrat chair over amendments
SUMMARY: Sen. Rand Paul, R-Ky., walked out of the Homeland Security hearing Wednesday after suggesting Sen. Gary Peters, D-Mich., was introducing a third-degree amendment to the Fire Grants and Safety Act.

TITLE: Minnesota Lt. Gov. ripped for saying parents must ‘believe’ when kids ‘tell us who they are’
SUMMARY: Minnesota Lt. Gov. Peggy Flanagan, a Democrat, argued parents must "believe" their children when they "tell us who they are" in a now-viral clip.

TITLE: Furman records first upset of 2023 March Madness, taking down Virginia with wild late sequence
SUMMARY: After not leading for the first 35 minutes of the game and trailing by as many as 12 points, No. 13 Furman fought back for the first upset of March Madness.

TITLE: Wellesley College says 'no plan' to revisit mission after students vote to admit trans men
SUMMARY: Wellesley College officials responded after Tuesday's student vote to admit transgender men to the all-women institution, reiterating that the college still focuses on women.

TITLE: NRCC drops ‘March to the Left Madness’ bracket as NCAA tournament kicks off
SUMMARY: Fox News Digital exclusively obtained National Republican Congressional Committee's "March to the Left Madness" bracket as March Madness officially kicks off.

TITLE: No charges for Detroit-area cop who shot armed suspect in police station lobby
SUMMARY: A Dearborn, Michigan police officer will not be charged for killing Ali Naji, who entered a police station lobby in December and attempted to shoot him.

TITLE: Georgia bill banning transgender surgeries on minors one step closer to becoming law
SUMMARY: Georgia lawmakers have advanced a controversial bill that would ban sex-reassignment surgeries and hormone replacement therapies for gender dysphoric minors.

TITLE: ND Supreme Court upholds injunction on state's plan to outlaw most abortions
SUMMARY: The North Dakota Supreme Court on Thursday ruled that an injunction on a law banning all abortions not performed in rape, incest or life-threatening situations will remain in place.

TITLE: Ben Affleck shares why he avoided working with Matt Damon
SUMMARY: Ben Affleck opened up on his friendship with Matt Damon and why they haven't worked together as much since the success of "Good Will Hunting."

TITLE: California church fights back after $2.8 million fine for defying COVID lockdown order
SUMMARY: Calvary Chapel in Silicon Valley is counter-suing Santa Clara County over nearly $3 million in fines accumulated for violating COVID-19 lockdown orders.

TITLE: Biden family received more than $1M from Hunter associate after 2017 China wire: House Oversight
SUMMARY: Biden family members received more than $1 million in payments from accounts related to Hunter Biden’s business associate Rob Walker and their Chinese business ventures in 2017.

TITLE: Russia flying more armed aircraft over US bases in Syria, US CENTCOM commander says
SUMMARY: U.S. Central Command has observed a concerning rise in "unprofessional" and "unsafe" behavior from Russian aircraft pilots near U.S. bases in Syria.
